{{Advert|date=August 2013}}
{{Infobox book | image = Chinese Medical Herbology & Pharmacology.jpg| | caption = Chinese Medical Herbology and Pharmacology Textbook | author = John K. Chen, Tina T. Chen | illustrator = | cover_artist = Charles Funk | country = USA | language = English | series = | subject = [[Chinese herbology]] | publisher = Art of Medicine Press | release_date = 2004 | media_type = Print <small>([[hardcover]])</small> | pages = 1336<ref>http://aompress.com/book_herbology/index.html</ref> | isbn = 0-9740635-0-9 | followed_by = [[Chinese Herbal Formulas and Applications]] }}
'''''Chinese Medical Herbology and Pharmacology''''' is a text on [[Chinese herbology]] by Dr. John K. Chen and Tina T. Chen. It is one of the few comprehensive texts on Chinese [[herbology]] in existence that has been published in the English and German language, and it is widely recognized by the [[oriental medicine]] community as both a valid teaching tool used in many [[oriental medicine]] universities in the US, as well as a reference book that is widely cited by many academic individuals and practitioners.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Typhonium Plus |url=http://www.typhoniumplus.com/chinese-medical-herbology.html |title=Chinese Medical Herbology Typhonium Plus |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.herbaltherapeutics.net/recommendedreading.htm |title=David's Recommended Reading List |publisher=Herbaltherapeutics.net |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aimc.edu/current-students/registrar/textbooks/ |title=Textbooks &#124; |publisher=Aimc.edu |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://aoma.edu/current-students/academics/textbooks/ |title=Textbooks - AOMA Graduate School of Integrative Medicine |publisher=Aoma.edu |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sacredlotus.com/about/references.cfm |title=Sacred Lotus Arts - References |publisher=Sacredlotus.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref> In addition to the traditional and modern uses of Chinese herbology, this text is also a tremendous source that details clinical studies and research, safety data and [[toxicology]], as well as western [[pharmacological]] and herb-drug interactions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilaaom.org/books.html |title=Book Reviews |publisher=Ilaaom.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.henriettesherbal.com/faqs/medi-6-1-books.html |title=6.1 Good Books on Herbs and Herbal Medicine &#124; Henriette's Herbal Homepage |publisher=Henriettesherbal.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref> This text is also part of the required knowledge from the national ([[NCCAOM]]) as well as many state [[Acupuncture]] licensing boards.<ref>http://www.nccaom.org/wp-content/uploads/pdf/Chinese%20Herbology%20Study%20Guide.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.acupuncture.ca.gov/students/exam_preparation</ref> It has been and continues to be cited in many published articles and papers on Chinese Herbal Medicine, especially those that cover the subject of pharmacological and herbal interactions.<ref>{{cite web|last=Shonez |first=Billy |url=http://www.nyctcm.edu/acupuncture-tcm-blog/2011/02/the-benefits-of-cinnamon.html |title=The Benefits of Cinnamon - Acupuncture & TCM Blog |publisher=Nyctcm.edu |date=2011-02-26 |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thieme-connect.com/ejournals/html/plantamedica/doi/10.1055/s-0029-1186218 |title=Thieme eJournals - Full Text Article |publisher=Thieme-connect.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cancerhelps.com/research/chinese_medical_herbology.htm |title=Chinese Medical Herbology and Pharmacology |publisher=Cancerhelps.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=MichaelW |url=http://www.livestrong.com/article/97251-chinese-healing-herbs-breast-cancer/ |title=Chinese Healing Herbs For Breast Cancer |publisher=Livestrong.Com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acupuncturetoday.com/mpacms/at/article.php?id=30404 |title=The Treatment of Pertussis (Whooping Cough) With Chinese Herbal Medicine, Part One |publisher=Acupuncturetoday.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-02}}</ref>
