{{Lowercase title}}
{{Infobox company | name = iStorez, Inc. | type = Private | foundation = 2006 | location = [[Sunnyvale, California|Sunnyvale]], [[California]], United States | key_people = Anand Jagannathan, Founder, President & CEO and Shabd Vaid, Co-founder, Vice President, Engineering & Operations | homepage = [http://www.istorez.com/ iStorez.com] }}
'''iStorez, Inc. ''' was a [[comparison shopping website]] that specialized in [[Discounts and allowances|discounted]] products.<ref>http://talkingshopping.com/talking/2008/12/new-shopping-site-istorez-debu.html</ref> It was acquired by [[TheFind]] in August 2009, likely for under $500,000.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://techcrunch.com/2009/09/01/thefind-acquires-istorezcom-to-help-consumers-find-deals-while-shopping/ | title=TheFind acquires iStorez.com to help consumers find deals while shopping | work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=1 September 2009 | accessdate=10 February 2014 | author=Leena Rao}}</ref>
== History == iStorez launched in beta on January 30, 2008,<ref>http://www.internetretailer.com/dailyNews.asp?id=25250</ref> and launched publicly on November 12, 2008.<ref>http://www.seattlepi.com/business/387415_onlinesavings12.html</ref> It was founded by Anand Jagannathan, CEO of parent company Kriyari, Inc., and founder of three other start-ups including Banyan Systems and Responsys. iStorez is headquartered in Sunnyvale, California.
== Business model == * iStorez allowed users to create a personal mall that reflects their favorite stores and styles, and to track trends and special promotions according to customized interests.<ref>http://www.marketingvox.com/istorez-to-sizzle-bacn-on-demand-036182/</ref> *It allowed visitors to shop by theme/category. For example, visitors can search for fashion trends, special occasions, holidays etc., or sort their search by price, size, personality or fabric texture.<ref>http://www.pressbox.co.uk/detailed/Consumer/iStorez_Launches_Introduces_a_Brand_New_Way_to_Shop_250964.html</ref> *iStorez widgets for [[facebook]], [[MySpace]] and other social networks allowed users to share information on [[fashion]] trends and shopping deals.<ref>https://venturebeat.com/2008/11/28/new-istorez-site-gives-users-the-scoop-on-black-friday/</ref>
== Industry Awards & Recognition == iStorez was a 2009 [[Software and Information Industry Association#CODiE Awards|Codie award]]s finalist for 'Best [[eCommerce]] Solution'.<ref>http://www.siia.net/codies/2009/finalist_list.asp</ref>
== References == {{reflist}}
