{{commerce-website-stub}}

[[File:Korean Central History Museum 01.jpg|thumb|The Korean Central History Museum in Pyongyang]]
The '''Korean Central History Museum''' is a [[museum]] located in [[Pyongyang]], [[North Korea]].<ref>[http://www.korea-dpr.com/museums.html Democratic People's Republic of Korea - Museums] ({{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6FbjIKDAB?url=http://www.korea-dpr.com/museums.html |date=April 3, 2013 }})</ref> It was established on December 1, 1945.<ref>{{cite web|title=Korean Central History Museum, Centre of History Education|url=http://www.vok.rep.kp/CBC/english.php|access-date=5 December 2015|publisher=Voice of Korea|quote=O Hae Ryong, Curator of the Korean Central History Memeum, says: 'The great leader Kim Il Sung, though busy with the building of a new country, established the present Korean Central History Museum on December 1, 1945.[']|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216050822/http://www.vok.rep.kp/CBC/english.php|archivedate=16 February 2016|df=}}</ref> It contains displays on Korean history from primitive society to the modern age.<ref>http://www.korea-dpr.com/museums.html</ref> The museum is located at the north end of [[Kim Il-sung Square]].

